<topic id="author-position-information">
  <title>Visual Hints for the Cursor Position</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Author editing mode<indexterm>Visual hints</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Author editing mode<indexterm>Tooltips</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Visual hints in Author mode</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_pvw_bgk_54b">When the cursor is positioned inside a new context, a tooltip will be shown for a couple of
      seconds displaying the position of the cursor relative to the context of the current
      element.</p>
    <p id="p_qvw_bgk_54b">Here are some of the common situations that can be encountered: </p>
    <ul id="ul_rvw_bgk_54b">
      <li id="li_svw_bgk_54b">
        <p id="p_tvw_bgk_54b"><b>Before first <term>block</term></b> - The cursor is positioned before the first <xref
            keyref="glossentry_block-element"><term>block</term></xref> child of the current
          node.</p>
        <p id="p_uvw_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/sa_position_tooltip_1.png" product="author editor"/><image
            href="../img/ec_position_tooltip_1.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"/>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li id="li_vvw_bgk_54b">
        <p id="p_wvw_bgk_54b"><b>Between two <term>block elements</term></b> - The cursor is positioned between two
            <xref keyref="glossentry_block-element"><term>block elements</term></xref>.</p>
        <p id="p_xvw_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/sa_position_tooltip_2.png" product="author editor"/><image
            href="../img/ec_position_tooltip_2.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"/>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li id="li_yvw_bgk_54b">
        <p id="p_zvw_bgk_54b"><b>After last <term>block</term></b> - The cursor is positioned after the last <xref
            keyref="glossentry_block-element"><term>block element</term></xref> child of the current
          node.</p>
        <p id="p_aww_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/sa_position_tooltip_3.png" product="author editor"/><image
            href="../img/ec_position_tooltip_3.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"/>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li id="li_bww_bgk_54b">
        <p id="p_cww_bgk_54b"><b>Inside a node</b> - The cursor is positioned inside a node.</p>
        <p id="p_dww_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/sa_position_tooltip_4.png" product="author editor"/><image
            href="../img/ec_position_tooltip_4.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"/>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li id="li_eww_bgk_54b">
        <p id="p_fww_bgk_54b"><b>Before an <term>inline element</term></b> - The cursor is positioned inside an
          element, before a child <xref keyref="glossentry_inline-element"><term>inline
              element</term></xref>.</p>
        <p id="p_gww_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/sa_position_tooltip_5.png" product="author editor"/><image
            href="../img/ec_position_tooltip_5.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"/>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li id="li_hww_bgk_54b">
        <p id="p_iww_bgk_54b"><b>Between two inline elements</b> - The cursor is positioned between two <xref
            keyref="glossentry_inline-element"><term>inline elements</term></xref>.</p>
        <p id="p_jww_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/sa_position_tooltip_6.png" product="author editor"/><image
            href="../img/ec_position_tooltip_6.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"/>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li id="li_kww_bgk_54b">
        <p id="p_lww_bgk_54b"><b>After an inline element</b> - The cursor is positioned inside an element, after a
          child <xref keyref="glossentry_inline-element"><term>inline element</term></xref>.</p>
        <p id="p_mww_bgk_54b"><image href="../img/sa_position_tooltip_7.png" product="author editor"/><image
            href="../img/ec_position_tooltip_7.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"/>
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p id="p_nww_bgk_54b">The nodes in these cases are displayed in the tooltip window using the element names.</p>
    <p id="p_oww_bgk_54b">To deactivate this feature, <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/>, go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Cursor Navigation</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>, and deselect the <xref
        href="caret-navigation.dita#caret-navigation/show-cursor-postion-tooltip"><uicontrol>Show
          cursor position tooltip</uicontrol> option</xref>. Even if this option is deselected, you
      can still display the position tooltip by pressing
        <uicontrol><shortcut>Shift+F2</shortcut></uicontrol>.</p>
    <note id="note_pww_bgk_54b">The position information tooltip is not displayed if <xref
        href="author-display-markup.dita#author-display-markup"><uicontrol>Full Tags with
          Attributes</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>Full Tags</uicontrol> is selected in the
            <uicontrol><image href="../img/TagsDrop.png" id="image_pmr_mhm_1s"/>Tags display
          mode</uicontrol> drop-down menu</xref>.</note>
    <section id="location_tooltip">
      <title>Location Tooltip</title>
      <p id="p_qww_bgk_54b">When editing XML documents in a visual environment, you might find it difficult to position
        the cursor between certain tags that do not have a visual representation. To counterbalance
        this, <ph keyref="product"/> displays a transparent preview of the position information,
        called the <uicontrol>Location Tooltip</uicontrol>:</p>
      <p id="p_rww_bgk_54b">
        <fig id="fig_sww_bgk_54b">
          <title>Location Tooltip</title>
          <image href="../img/GhostCaret.png" placement="inline"/>
        </fig>
      </p>
      <p id="p_tww_bgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> displays a <uicontrol>Location Tooltip</uicontrol> when the
        following conditions are met:<ul id="ul_uww_bgk_54b">
          <li id="li_vww_bgk_54b">You are editing the document in one of the following <xref
              href="author-display-markup.dita#author-display-markup">tags display modes</xref>:
              <uicontrol>Inline Tags</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Partial Tags</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>No
              Tags</uicontrol>.</li>
          <li id="li_www_bgk_54b">The mouse pointer is moved between <xref keyref="glossentry_block-element"><term>block
                elements</term></xref>.</li>
        </ul></p>
      <p id="p_xww_bgk_54b">To activate or deactivate this feature, use the <xref
          href="caret-navigation.dita#caret-navigation/show-location-tooltip"><uicontrol>Show
            location tooltip on mouse move</uicontrol> option</xref> in the <xref
          href="caret-navigation.dita#caret-navigation"><uicontrol>Cursor Navigation</uicontrol>
          preferences page</xref>.</p>
    </section>
  </body>
